narrative: 21 YEAR OLD MALE PEDESTRIAN WALKED AROUND THE LOWERED GATES INTO THE PATH OF WESTBOUND EQUIPMENT TRAIN - IGNORING SIGNALS AND HORN OF EQUIPMENT.  IT IS ASSUMED THAT THE PEDESTRIAN BELIEVED THE TRAIN WAS MAKING A STATION STOP AT THE STATION JUST EAST OF THE CROSSING.NoneNone
reporting_railroad_smt_grouping: SMT-1 - Amtrak and Commuter East, some Tourist/Historic
maintenance_railroad_smt_grouping: SMT-1 - Amtrak and Commuter East, some Tourist/Historic

narrative: MOTOR VEHICLE OPERATOR WENT AROUND CROSSING GATES THAT WERE FUNCTIONING PROPERLY AND IN DOWN POSITION AT THE ELEVENTH STREET IN HUNTINGTON AND THE VEHICLE WAS STRUCK BY WESTBOUND TRAIN NUMBER 4713 ONTHE PORT JEFFERSON BRANCH.  THE DRIVER AND ONE PASSENGER IN THE MOTOR VEHICLE WERE KILLED.  THE OTHER PASSENGER IN THE MOTOR VEHICLE WAS SERIOUSLY INJURED.  TRAIN INVOLVED WAS A NON-PASSENGER EQUIPMENT TRAIN AND THE TRAIN CREW PERSONNEL DID NOT REPORT INJURY AS A RESULT OF THIS INCIDENT.
